vcprompt
------------------------------------------
vcprompt is a little C program that prints a short string with barebones
information about the current working directory for various version control
systems. You configure your shell to include the output of vcprompt in your
prompt, and you get version control information in your prompt.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.4-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-2
  binutils-2.45-1
  cygport-0.37.2-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/wfr/vcprompt

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/wfr/vcprompt/archive/refs/tags/1.3.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack vcprompt-1.3.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./vcprompt-1.3.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/vcprompt-1.3.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/vcprompt-1.3.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(vcprompt)
  /usr/bin/vcprompt.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/vcprompt.README
  /usr/share/doc/vcprompt/README.md
  /usr/share/doc/vcprompt/release.txt
  /usr/share/man/man1/vcprompt.1.gz

